One (1) janitorial uniform consistent with the uniforms given to custodians of the school, consisting of: one (1) pair of navy blue pants, one (1) navy blue jacket with the lettering: “███████ High School” on the back, one (1) brown or black belt, and one (1) white or gray dress shirt.
附加记录：    

This  notation ruins articles for me. I understand that apparently, it's some sort of actual thing that's done in legal documents or whatever to make sure that number amounts are made perfectly clear. Something like that. But it just always comes across as unnecessary junk text that disrupts the flow of the document, especially when multiple numbers come up in a small amount of space. It makes me want to stop reading, almost.

Other than my annoyance with that notation, I think the document itself is decently presented. The tone isn't bad and I didn't notice any particularly egregious issues. The anomaly itself doesn't really do much for me, and there's some issues I have with a few things, like the very specific  of the time that it takes for things to happen, the fact that the Foundation felt the need to have three armed agents present in that first test, and the lengthy explanation of details of the anomaly that probably would've been better left unexplained, among other things.

It's a big article, I don't want to go line-by-line picking apart everything I didn't like about it. But the long and short of it is that I couldn't like this one. -1.







